AB  - Advanced artificial intelligence (AI)-driven futuristic support technologies have transformed a number of industries and changed how people engage with technology. OpenAI’s ChatGPT, a state-of-the-art artificial intelligence model for language processing, is one such innovative creation. The Generative Pre-trained Transformer (GPT) architecture serves as the foundation for ChatGPT. Online, ChatGPT has been growing rapidly. Through the use of commands, people can have conversations with the AI through this chatbot, which is based on OpenAI’s language model. ChatGPT has limitations even if it’s great and yields amazing outcomes when creating stories, poems, songs, essays, and other types of writing. The bot is available for users to ask inquiries, and it will respond with relevant and persuasive topics and answers. These days, ChatGPT is at the top of many academic agendas. In response to the tools, administrators form task forces and call institution-wide meetings; the general consensus is to embrace this technology. This study examines ChatGPT’s prospects, difficulties, most recent developments, and future directions as well as its effects in a variety of industries, including customer service, healthcare, education, and more. We explore ChatGPT’s potential, assessing the state of the field and speculating on how it can affect society. We also consider any potential drawbacks, including issues with data privacy, trouble understanding complex concepts, potentially misleading information, and accessibility issues. Lastly, we outline possible applications for ChatGPT in educational institutions and future research directions, emphasizing its usefulness as a support for instruction, a tool for teachers’ professional development, and a way to boost administrative efficiency. Our examination shows that ChatGPT has a lot of potential to change the advanced education area, despite a few shortcomings that still need to be handled. © The Author(s), under exclusive licen